latestIgtvVideos.title: QnA - but a good one. In collaboration with @tedxgoldenbridge
latestIgtvVideos.caption:
Happy World Photography Day to you all. Here's a fun, short interview of mine with @tedxgoldenbridge of ever so frequently asked questions. 

Hope you enjoy! 

I have always been fascinated by stories.

My parents had a camera finely wrapped and safeguarded in one of those steel almirahs. It used to come out in occasions such as birthdays, school functions, and when we went on a family trips. Irrespective of whatever the occasion was, my mother’s Kodak KB10 would seize the moment in time with a neon yellow date stamped at the bottom right corner. My eyes would light up when I would see the device, baffled about how one button could capture a myriad of moments. I vividly remember holding it in my hands and posing like one of those photographer s I admired.

As a photographer who also so happens to be a woman, one of the rare kinds in the City of Joy, I knew I cannot afford to be a pushover. Photography enabled me to work with global names across the country, for fashion, editorials, advertising campaigns, and they all culminated in me building my brand.

There is something profound about photography and undoubtedly there’s more than one reason why I choose to explore this visual expression of art. I have always been agog in understanding what the world really looks like. What it really is.

The world, the individuality, the joy of looking individually at the world - it's worth being greater, better than the sum of its parts.

Video shot by @offbeatfilmmaker

#interview #photographer

latestIgtvVideos.title: #RediscoverAgra with @courtyardbymarriottagra X Upahar Biswas
latestIgtvVideos.caption:
If you wonder what to expect in this video? It's a 3 mins video of birds flying over #jamamasjid , watching little kids pose for my camera, women at #mehtabbagh finds a moment for this new visitor, #blacktajmahal wakes up under the white sky, Nani ji sells bangles with the sunniest smile, #masalagali sees a usual day making profit, #munnalal pethe wale sells the sweetest petha, #lalachimanlal sells the same best puri sabji platter, as the restaurant at Marriott prepares for the newest bento boxes and grill by the pool. Not to miss the carpets making the largest market in India and marbles carving into our beloved monument in the City of Love.

It was a challenge showing this beautiful city in 3 mins, but if you like it, do drop a comment below.

latestIgtvVideos.title: Coronavirus does not discriminate, then why do you?
latestIgtvVideos.caption:
The COVID-19 pandemic has not only disrupted lives and altered the socioeconomic paradigm, but it has also held a mirror to each of our faces. Now is the time to change, not just to adapt but to also rectify our flaws. Racism is one of the social ills that must be eradicated from our mind scape. When a virus doesn't discriminate between the lives it affects, who are we to racially profile others?

Remember, an inclusive society is a future-facing society. Change today for a better tomorrow.
Share the message, talk about it, let your voice be heard.

@meghdutroychowdhury what a pleasure partnering with someone like you who is passionate about changing the narrative around the city of Kolkata and care deeply about building meaning in field of education.

Thank You @sanghamitrac and @readersdigestindia for coming ahead and joining hands, only to make the fist stronger. Associating with people who speaks against injustice is all we need now and forever.

Thanks to @debby_tungnung @that_girl_from_jupiter_ @yourfujoshi.senpai  @padmasangmubmzn  and @franceslepcha for standing against odds talking about experiences so that the next person doesn't have to.

@amiutsab and @sayan22e keep inspiring me.

Thank you @writu_raj
